WEBVTT

00:15.783 --> 00:21.520
<i> [laidback music playing]</i>

00:21.522 --> 00:23.522
- I hope I didn't startle you.

00:23.524 --> 00:26.091
Sometimes I startle people.

00:26.093 --> 00:30.029
- No, you're cool.

00:30.031 --> 00:32.798
- What do you say, Harry?
Want to dance?

00:32.800 --> 00:34.400
♪ ♪

00:34.402 --> 00:36.301
- You all by your lonesome,
sister?

00:36.303 --> 00:38.470
- For once in my life.

00:38.472 --> 00:40.039
- What can I do you for?

00:40.041 --> 00:41.340
- Dance with me.

00:41.342 --> 00:43.575
- Yeah?
[chuckles]

00:43.577 --> 00:44.643
♪ ♪

00:44.645 --> 00:46.412
Where'd you come from?

00:46.414 --> 00:49.214
- You don't remember me,
do you, Harry?

00:49.216 --> 00:51.417
♪ ♪

00:51.419 --> 00:53.552
- Tuesday night.

00:53.554 --> 00:55.621
You were in here
with some big guy.

00:55.623 --> 00:57.156
- Well, he's gone now.

00:57.158 --> 00:59.491
- [chuckles]
Yeah, well...

00:59.493 --> 01:02.528
Stupid him.

01:02.530 --> 01:04.830
- Oh.

01:04.832 --> 01:06.832
- [grunting]

01:06.834 --> 01:08.567
You're not a woman,
are you?

01:08.569 --> 01:09.768
- Hmm.

01:09.770 --> 01:11.670
- You're one of them shifters.

01:11.672 --> 01:13.672
- It was foretold.

01:13.674 --> 01:16.809
- Foretell it again.
I'm all ears.

01:16.811 --> 01:19.378
- We're looking for them.

01:19.380 --> 01:21.213
And you...

01:21.215 --> 01:23.082
are not one of them.

01:23.084 --> 01:25.818
- [groaning]

01:40.101 --> 01:42.835
<i> - Why is Idaho</i>
<i> the place to go this season?</i>

01:42.837 --> 01:44.603
<i> Maybe it's because the spuds</i>
<i> have eyes</i>

01:44.605 --> 01:46.438
<i> and have been watching us.</i>

01:46.440 --> 01:49.775
<i>But then I realized that sounds</i>
<i> like foolishness and lies--</i>

01:49.777 --> 01:52.811
- Seems like Idaho's
the place to be.

01:52.813 --> 01:54.246
- Hey, hey.

01:54.248 --> 01:55.347
Something's going on.

01:55.349 --> 01:57.349
- Holy shit.
- I'll go.

01:57.351 --> 01:59.351
Everybody arm up.
- Maybe not.

01:59.353 --> 02:00.619
- Okay.
- No, no, no.

02:00.621 --> 02:02.121
- I got this.
- No, no, no, no.

02:02.123 --> 02:03.422
We talk first.

02:03.424 --> 02:04.790
- Talk? What do you want
to talk about?

02:04.792 --> 02:06.558
- Go with your father.
Back him up.

02:06.560 --> 02:08.594
- Not with that.
Not with that.

02:08.596 --> 02:10.629
- They're gonna eat us alive.

02:10.631 --> 02:12.664
- Fine, I'll go.
You stay here.

02:12.666 --> 02:15.234
Follow the plan, okay?

02:15.236 --> 02:17.903
Follow the plan.
Girls, arm up.

02:17.905 --> 02:18.904
- Hey.

02:18.906 --> 02:21.340
Hey.

02:21.342 --> 02:22.574
Just passing through.

02:22.576 --> 02:24.176
Headed east.

02:33.821 --> 02:35.354
- You up for this?

02:38.192 --> 02:39.858
- Yeah, I'll talk to 'em.

02:45.166 --> 02:48.800
You are in hostile
territory, man.

02:48.802 --> 02:51.270
There's a toll.

02:51.272 --> 02:53.805
- We have some food,
not much.

02:53.807 --> 02:55.941
Couple of firearms
we could spare.

02:55.943 --> 02:58.810
- [laughs]
Merry Christmas to me, huh?

02:58.812 --> 03:01.280
- You should take it.
I'm respecting your toll.

03:01.282 --> 03:03.715
- How'd you last so long
since end days?

03:03.717 --> 03:04.716
[gun cocks]

03:04.718 --> 03:05.817
- I got it.

03:05.819 --> 03:07.219
- No, I got it.

03:07.221 --> 03:08.353
[rifle clicks]

03:08.355 --> 03:10.822
- No, you don't.

03:10.824 --> 03:13.258
<i> [tense music]</i>

03:13.260 --> 03:14.960
- Put the guns down.

03:14.962 --> 03:17.462
- That doesn't seem safe.

03:17.464 --> 03:19.298
- Guns down, kids.

03:19.300 --> 03:20.766
- We got a standoff here
anyway.

03:20.768 --> 03:21.833
- No, we don't.

03:21.835 --> 03:24.269
I win.
- Oh, how do you figure?

03:24.271 --> 03:25.537
Ooh-hoo.

03:25.539 --> 03:27.506
- You're already dead to me.

03:27.508 --> 03:32.411
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:32.413 --> 03:35.314
- Guns down, boys.

03:35.316 --> 03:37.349
Hey, Karen.

03:37.351 --> 03:38.817
- Kids?

03:40.554 --> 03:42.621
[sighs]
Meet Grandpa.

03:42.623 --> 03:47.926
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:47.928 --> 03:50.896
<i> [ominous music]</i>

03:50.898 --> 03:58.237
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:58.239 --> 04:01.707
- Yeah, we got everything
from chefs to snipers

04:01.709 --> 04:03.375
to live entertainment...

04:03.377 --> 04:05.611
although, to be honest,
most of that sucks.

04:05.613 --> 04:07.546
Hell, we even got a missus
around here someone

04:07.548 --> 04:08.914
does pedicures.

04:08.916 --> 04:11.283
Hold your fire there, Connor,
just for a minute.

04:11.285 --> 04:13.619
- Impressive, Ewan.
There's a lot of cohesion.

04:13.621 --> 04:16.355
- I don't know what that is,
but it sounds good.

04:16.357 --> 04:17.956
See, your brainiac
likes me, daughter.

04:17.958 --> 04:19.291
- He doesn't know you yet.

04:19.293 --> 04:20.959
- I like you, Josh.

04:20.961 --> 04:22.894
- You got plenty
of power too.

04:22.896 --> 04:25.864
- That's right.
Electricity too.

04:25.866 --> 04:27.966
That was a joke.
I swear.

04:29.036 --> 04:30.936
Say, you gals.

04:30.938 --> 04:32.871
You tough like your mama,
or are you smart

04:32.873 --> 04:34.506
like your old man?

04:34.508 --> 04:36.408
- My mom's smart.
- And Dad's tough.

04:36.410 --> 04:38.610
- You, you're a pharaoh,
just like me.

04:38.612 --> 04:40.646
- Ugh.
- I can see it in your eyes.

04:40.648 --> 04:43.382
- Is that a good thing?
- No.

04:43.384 --> 04:46.285
- Hey, my super soldiers--
Scott, Rafaella.

04:46.287 --> 04:48.287
This is my grandson.

04:48.289 --> 04:50.689
This is my daughter,
her twins, and her husband.

04:50.691 --> 04:51.923
- How you doing?

04:51.925 --> 04:53.425
<i> What is this place, Ewan?</i>

04:53.427 --> 04:56.828
- Basically,
it's a no-class paradise.

04:56.830 --> 04:57.996
- And?

04:57.998 --> 04:59.598
- What do you mean
by "and"?

04:59.600 --> 05:01.500
- You have a social system here.

05:01.502 --> 05:03.035
One person does nails.
Another one kills.

05:03.037 --> 05:04.803
People don't do those things
for nothing.

05:04.805 --> 05:07.906
- They get my protection,
to start with.

05:07.908 --> 05:11.376
And we also operate
a small manufacturing business.

05:11.378 --> 05:12.511
- No one needs your meth.

05:12.513 --> 05:13.945
The world is meth.

05:13.947 --> 05:15.947
- Meth? Hell, no.
I've gone legit.

05:15.949 --> 05:17.449
- Bullshit.

05:17.451 --> 05:19.351
- Let me show you something.

05:19.353 --> 05:20.552
Come out back to the lab.

05:20.554 --> 05:22.421
- What an asshole.

05:22.423 --> 05:24.523
- This here is the chemist.

05:24.525 --> 05:26.958
We almost lost him
a few years back

05:26.960 --> 05:28.560
when his laboratory exploded.

05:28.562 --> 05:30.362
He's like you, Doc--
a brainiac.

05:30.364 --> 05:32.030
- Hi, I'm Josh.

05:32.032 --> 05:33.799
- [laughs]

05:33.801 --> 05:36.034
What he lacks in personality,

05:36.036 --> 05:38.970
he makes up for in chemistry.

05:38.972 --> 05:42.007
We're in the
tetracycline business.

05:42.009 --> 05:44.476
- So why did you jack us
on the road?

05:44.478 --> 05:46.578
- Got to cover costs.

05:46.580 --> 05:48.080
- So you're charging for meds.

05:48.082 --> 05:49.948
- People pay
with what they've got--

05:49.950 --> 05:51.883
gold, jewelry, livestock.

05:51.885 --> 05:54.519
But it doesn't give us
regular funding.

05:54.521 --> 05:55.721
- So just to be clear,

05:55.723 --> 05:57.756
you are charging people
to save them?

05:57.758 --> 05:59.057
- Yeah, but not much.

05:59.059 --> 06:00.559
And he is helping 'em.

06:00.561 --> 06:02.527
Hey, girls, let's go.

06:02.529 --> 06:05.497
We don't want to end up
like the chemist there.

06:05.499 --> 06:06.498
- See you later.

06:06.500 --> 06:08.400
- Sally's dead.

06:11.004 --> 06:12.971
So you're saving
people's lives.

06:12.973 --> 06:14.806
You're gonna charge
anybody for it.

06:24.518 --> 06:26.051
- Play "Free Bird."

06:26.053 --> 06:27.919
- I'm not playing
no God damn "Free Bird."

06:27.921 --> 06:29.454
- Play God damn "Free Bird"!

06:29.456 --> 06:30.722
- No!
Get out!

06:30.724 --> 06:31.957
- Come on!
Play that shit!

06:31.959 --> 06:32.958
- Get out of my face.

06:32.960 --> 06:34.059
- I'll kill you!

06:34.061 --> 06:35.460
- Kill him!

06:36.697 --> 06:38.563
- Ease off.

06:38.565 --> 06:40.532
- Prick's been playing
Billy Joel since Friday.

06:40.534 --> 06:42.134
- Even I want to kill you
when you do that.

06:42.136 --> 06:43.535
- Where's Matt?

06:43.537 --> 06:47.038
- He's at the bar,
making friends.

06:47.040 --> 06:48.607
- Holy crap.

06:48.609 --> 06:50.509
That's a Ponaturi head.

06:53.147 --> 06:54.713
Who killed the Ponaturi?

06:57.718 --> 06:59.651
- I did.

06:59.653 --> 07:01.586
Whiskey.

07:01.588 --> 07:03.922
- Same here.

07:03.924 --> 07:06.158
Killed one too.
Where was yours?

07:06.160 --> 07:08.627
- Saddle River.
Yours?

07:08.629 --> 07:10.762
- Seattle.
Came up through the drain.

07:10.764 --> 07:12.197
- You're in Seattle?
- Yeah.

07:12.199 --> 07:13.698
- Is it really like they say?

07:13.700 --> 07:15.100
- No one left.

07:15.102 --> 07:17.169
- Huh.

07:25.979 --> 07:28.113
- That's are own chickens
from out back.

07:28.115 --> 07:30.115
- So they're technically
free-range.

07:30.117 --> 07:33.585
- Well, they were running around
45 minutes ago.

07:33.587 --> 07:35.020
- All right.
Well, it's time to go.

07:35.022 --> 07:38.690
- Nah.
One beer with your old man.

07:38.692 --> 07:40.525
Come on.

07:40.527 --> 07:41.927
Yeah.
[chuckles]

07:41.929 --> 07:44.029
Here you go.
- Thanks.

07:44.031 --> 07:45.831
- Yeah.

07:47.634 --> 07:50.836
- [laughs]
- What?

07:50.838 --> 07:53.038
- Everyone's vegan
till there's fried chicken.

07:53.040 --> 07:54.473
- I'm not vegan.

07:54.475 --> 07:55.774
- You lie.

07:55.776 --> 07:57.709
- I started eating meat again,
like, two years ago.

07:57.711 --> 07:59.878
How'd you not remember that?

07:59.880 --> 08:01.112
- I don't know.

08:01.114 --> 08:03.048
Maybe you're not
as interesting as you think.

08:03.050 --> 08:05.250
- Well, maybe
you're not as hot.

08:05.252 --> 08:07.752
- That's a bitchy thing
to say.

08:07.754 --> 08:09.254
- Yeah, I know.
It was more your style.

08:11.058 --> 08:14.526
Wow.
We are stressed.

08:14.528 --> 08:15.827
- Yeah, I know.

08:15.829 --> 08:17.162
- All we've done
for the past two weeks

08:17.164 --> 08:19.865
is almost die.

08:19.867 --> 08:21.199
- Mm-hmm.

08:21.201 --> 08:22.901
Skinwalkers.

08:22.903 --> 08:24.870
Comets.

08:24.872 --> 08:26.137
Devyn.

08:26.139 --> 08:28.073
- Martin.

08:28.075 --> 08:30.609
Sweet Martin.

08:30.611 --> 08:33.945
- Okay, I'm getting us
some serious off time tonight.

08:33.947 --> 08:36.014
- Well, how--how serious?

08:36.016 --> 08:37.983
- [whispers]
Off the scale.

08:37.985 --> 08:39.618
- Okay, well,
who's coming with us

08:39.620 --> 08:40.819
on this time off?

08:40.821 --> 08:43.788
- I don't...
know yet.

08:43.790 --> 08:45.824
But there will be
competing offers.

08:45.826 --> 08:48.026
Come on.

08:48.028 --> 08:50.195
- So you're hanging out here
for a while.

08:50.197 --> 08:51.763
- Well...

08:51.765 --> 08:54.132
- Like I said, we have
a lot of road to cover.

08:54.134 --> 08:56.067
- Don't make any decisions

08:56.069 --> 08:58.603
till you have a look
at the honeymoon suite.

08:58.605 --> 09:01.673
You've been in that motorhome
since this thing started, right?

09:01.675 --> 09:04.309
- Oh, yeah, it's...

09:04.311 --> 09:05.911
complicated.

09:05.913 --> 09:07.279
- And how much
do you sleep at night?

09:07.281 --> 09:08.780
Three, four hours?

09:08.782 --> 09:10.882
- Well, we take shifts.
It works out.

09:10.884 --> 09:12.784
- Take an afternoon off.

09:12.786 --> 09:15.687
There ain't no place
more secure than this.

09:15.689 --> 09:18.557
You could catch up
on your...shut-eye.

09:18.559 --> 09:19.758
- Oh...
- In the honeymoon suite.

09:19.760 --> 09:22.294
- We have kids.

09:22.295 --> 09:24.829
- Hey, I owe you
20 years of babysitting,

09:24.831 --> 09:27.265
and I would love
to get to know them.

09:27.267 --> 09:29.834
No way of knowing how
this end-time bullshit's

09:29.836 --> 09:34.673
gonna turn out,
but having them here,

09:34.675 --> 09:37.342
little piece of heaven for me.

09:37.344 --> 09:40.078
- [sighs]

09:40.080 --> 09:42.781
What do you think?

09:49.289 --> 09:51.189
[both laugh]

09:57.631 --> 09:59.864
- So, uh, you like bikes?

09:59.866 --> 10:01.166
- Rode dirt all my life.

10:01.168 --> 10:02.300
Almost died three times.

10:02.302 --> 10:03.969
- [laughs]
How about hogs?

10:03.971 --> 10:05.303
- Ride my friend's,

10:05.305 --> 10:07.172
but it's not worth the fight
to own one, though.

10:07.174 --> 10:09.374
- Yeah, it's 'cause
they remind your mother of me.

10:09.376 --> 10:11.610
But if I were to give you one,

10:11.612 --> 10:14.112
she wouldn't really have any say
in the matter, would she?

10:14.114 --> 10:16.748
- Right. You're just
gonna give me a bike.

10:16.750 --> 10:18.717
- Take your pick.

10:18.719 --> 10:20.251
- Whose are they?

10:20.253 --> 10:22.954
- End times has
a high mortality rate, son.

10:22.956 --> 10:24.656
These are surplus.

10:24.658 --> 10:26.257
Which one do you like?

10:26.259 --> 10:28.059
- Sportster.

10:28.061 --> 10:29.761
- Oh, you got taste.

10:29.763 --> 10:31.296
Yeah, the custom 1200.

10:31.298 --> 10:33.798
Had my eye on that
for a second ride,

10:33.800 --> 10:34.799
but you want it?

10:34.801 --> 10:36.401
It's yours.

10:36.403 --> 10:37.736
- You're not gonna miss it?

10:37.738 --> 10:39.771
- Be happy to know
you're on it.

10:39.773 --> 10:44.109
Plus, I was hoping
that you would stay--

10:44.111 --> 10:46.211
you and your family.

10:46.213 --> 10:50.215
- Yeah, I don't know how happy
Mom would be with that.

10:50.217 --> 10:51.750
She's got issues.

10:51.752 --> 10:53.184
- [chuckles]
You're a grown man, Matt.

10:53.186 --> 10:54.886
You don't need
your mother's permission

10:54.888 --> 10:56.655
to stay and help me
run things.

10:56.657 --> 10:57.722
- Run things?

10:57.724 --> 10:59.157
- Raf is my right hand,

10:59.159 --> 11:01.359
and she's got great stuff
for a girl her age,

11:01.361 --> 11:04.195
but she's not family.

11:04.197 --> 11:07.966
If you were here,
you would be my number two.

11:11.238 --> 11:13.038
Check it out.
Go on.

11:13.040 --> 11:14.839
[chuckles]

11:19.980 --> 11:21.780
- [sighs]

11:23.350 --> 11:25.116
- How's that feel?

11:25.118 --> 11:27.252
- About right.

11:27.254 --> 11:28.953
- [laughs] Yeah.

11:36.029 --> 11:37.162
- Oh.

11:37.164 --> 11:38.863
- I'm amazed
we can still do that.

11:38.865 --> 11:40.398
- Yeah?

11:41.702 --> 11:43.134
It's simply like...

11:43.136 --> 11:44.369
- Don't say
"riding a bike."

11:44.371 --> 11:46.805
I hate riding bikes.

11:49.042 --> 11:50.275
- You gonna get some sleep?

11:50.277 --> 11:51.443
- Mm.

11:51.445 --> 11:53.178
No, I have to stay up
for the kids.

11:53.180 --> 11:54.379
- No, come on,
they're fine.

11:54.381 --> 11:56.448
I think...
you need a break.

11:56.450 --> 11:58.083
They could use one too.

11:58.085 --> 12:00.185
- Yeah, and what about you?

12:00.187 --> 12:02.721
- I want to go back
to that tetra lab,

12:02.723 --> 12:05.223
talk to that chemist
about how he makes that stuff.

12:05.225 --> 12:06.424
- Mm.

12:16.470 --> 12:19.170
- Three gold bars.
Offer him two.

12:19.172 --> 12:21.439
If he makes a fuss,
give him the other one.

12:21.441 --> 12:23.208
- I got it.

12:23.210 --> 12:24.743
- Where you guys going?

12:24.745 --> 12:27.746
- The locals around here
don't exactly like us.

12:27.748 --> 12:29.447
They keep dicking
with our ethanol supply,

12:29.449 --> 12:30.782
and we need it to make tetra.

12:30.784 --> 12:32.517
But we know a guy who's got

12:32.519 --> 12:35.320
a distillery,
runs a bar nearby.

12:35.322 --> 12:36.855
- You can come, if you want.

12:36.857 --> 12:39.090
- Love to.

12:39.092 --> 12:40.458
You guys want to--

12:40.460 --> 12:41.426
- Is there gonna be liquor?

12:41.428 --> 12:43.828
- Hell, yeah.

12:43.830 --> 12:45.330
both: We're in.
- Hop in.

12:45.332 --> 12:48.133
- Raf, they don't come back,
you don't come back.

12:50.437 --> 12:52.303
[engine turns over]

12:56.810 --> 12:59.477
You guard them with your life!

12:59.479 --> 13:00.812
- Drama queen.

13:00.814 --> 13:02.781
- Shut up.

13:04.918 --> 13:06.551
-<i> Please.</i>
<i> You have to help us.</i>

13:06.553 --> 13:09.454
<i> I gave him your tetra,</i>
<i> but he got worse.</i>

13:09.456 --> 13:12.791
- [coughs]

13:12.793 --> 13:15.927
- You have to do something
for him.

13:15.929 --> 13:17.462
- Absolutely,
we'll take care of him.

13:17.464 --> 13:19.397
Don't you worry.

13:19.399 --> 13:22.367
<i> [ominous music]</i>

13:25.806 --> 13:27.272
<i> - [screaming]</i>

13:27.274 --> 13:28.807
<i> - That's my sister.</i>

13:28.809 --> 13:30.842
<i>I will kill this man right now.</i>
<i> You know that.</i>

13:30.844 --> 13:33.311
<i> She gave that life for us.</i>
<i> Let's not forget it.</i>

13:33.313 --> 13:35.814
<i> Where's my daughter?</i>
<i> - What have you done?</i>

13:35.816 --> 13:37.982
<i> - The bodies on the ground?</i>
<i> - They got what they needed.</i>

13:37.984 --> 13:41.019
<i> - Brianna!</i>
<i> - [screaming]</i>

13:41.021 --> 13:43.521
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

13:55.101 --> 13:57.135
- So Harry owns this bar
and makes ethanol,

13:57.137 --> 13:59.838
which you buy with gold bars
and use to make tetra?

13:59.840 --> 14:01.573
- Nothing gets by you.

