what you're thinking here,

28:40.286 --> 28:41.985
and I'd probably be
thinking the same thing

28:41.987 --> 28:43.187
in your position.

28:43.189 --> 28:47.324
But I have had
a true conversion.

28:47.326 --> 28:49.860
I am doing good things.

28:49.862 --> 28:53.931
I'm getting all these people
through this end-world shit.

28:53.933 --> 28:56.200
And I want your family
to be a part of that.

28:56.202 --> 28:57.768
- Okay, I appreciate that,

28:57.770 --> 29:00.070
but we're--we're probably
gonna do it our own way.

29:00.072 --> 29:03.207
- Oh, right,
by understanding?

29:03.209 --> 29:06.410
- Yes.
- That's bullshit, man.

29:06.412 --> 29:09.413
It's not enough
to know what it is.

29:09.415 --> 29:12.316
You've got to beat it.

29:12.318 --> 29:15.919
- So you do it your way,
and we'll do it ours.

29:15.921 --> 29:17.821
Plus, you got
those people killed.

29:17.823 --> 29:20.491
I mean, come on.
Obviously.

29:22.862 --> 29:27.231
- And you would tell
my daughter this?

29:31.070 --> 29:35.272
They'll make it look
like you went down fighting.

29:35.274 --> 29:38.509
That's all I can do
for you now.

29:38.511 --> 29:40.811
- Here it comes, big boy.

29:40.813 --> 29:43.046
Open!

29:43.048 --> 29:45.249
Acid?
- No, I switched to peyote.

29:45.251 --> 29:46.350
Makes them more mellow.

29:46.352 --> 29:48.085
- Hey, let me try some.

29:48.087 --> 29:49.319
The wife says
I got to quit acid.

29:49.321 --> 29:50.954
- First one's free.

29:50.956 --> 29:53.223
- This guy's kind of a big one.
He's heavy.

29:53.225 --> 29:55.159
- Well, it takes 20 minutes
for the peyote to set in.

29:55.161 --> 29:57.027
He'll just be flying
into the van.

29:57.029 --> 29:58.095
I won't even need your help.

29:58.097 --> 29:59.963
- Okay.

30:01.400 --> 30:04.368
- Josh!

30:10.576 --> 30:11.942
Josh!

30:11.944 --> 30:13.210
-<i> We need to find Brianna.</i>

30:13.212 --> 30:14.511
- And Scott.

30:14.513 --> 30:16.446
If the locals sliced up Harry
for dealing with us,

30:16.448 --> 30:17.981
they won't think twice
about Scott...

30:17.983 --> 30:18.982
or your sister.

30:18.984 --> 30:21.118
- Who, me?

30:21.120 --> 30:22.586
- We didn't hear you
come in.

30:22.588 --> 30:24.254
- I am so happy to see you.

30:24.256 --> 30:25.522
Harry's dead.

30:25.524 --> 30:26.990
- Harry.

30:26.992 --> 30:28.559
- Look, whoever killed him
could still be here.

30:28.561 --> 30:30.127
We got to be careful.

30:30.129 --> 30:31.295
- You see Scott?

30:31.297 --> 30:32.429
- Scott?

30:32.431 --> 30:34.131
- The guy whose truck
you stole.

30:34.133 --> 30:35.966
- He's right outside.

30:35.968 --> 30:39.436
- Look, I am so sorry
about what I said earlier.

30:39.438 --> 30:40.470
- Sure.

30:40.472 --> 30:41.939
- You were right.

30:41.941 --> 30:44.208
I--I didn't really want you
to go away.

30:44.210 --> 30:46.009
- Guys, Scott's not outside.

30:46.011 --> 30:47.377
Where the hell is he?

30:47.379 --> 30:49.346
- I don't know.

30:49.348 --> 30:50.881
- Okay, let's radio Ewan.

30:50.883 --> 30:52.149
Tell him to get here stat.

30:54.186 --> 30:55.352
- On it.

31:00.593 --> 31:03.594
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

31:03.596 --> 31:07.898
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

31:10.569 --> 31:12.402
<i> - How's the ride?</i>

31:12.404 --> 31:14.238
- It's good.

31:14.240 --> 31:15.973
- [laughs]

31:15.975 --> 31:18.442
- What is it?
- Peyote.

31:18.444 --> 31:20.544
- It kicks like a mule.

31:20.546 --> 31:22.212
I don't want to die.

31:22.214 --> 31:24.448
- The whole world's ending hard.

31:24.450 --> 31:28.652
A couple of swings,
and your troubles are over.

31:28.654 --> 31:30.621
I'll tell you what, though.

31:30.623 --> 31:35.459
I'll let you go
for one last run.

31:36.662 --> 31:39.529
I love watching the vics run
on peyote.

31:39.531 --> 31:41.298
It's hysterical.

31:41.300 --> 31:43.033
- My name is Josh.

31:43.035 --> 31:45.435
- Goat. Nice to meet you.

31:45.437 --> 31:47.437
Oh! Oh!

31:47.439 --> 31:50.474
- Yeah, nice.

31:50.476 --> 31:53.076
Hey, you.

32:02.655 --> 32:04.354
- Where's Josh?
I can't find him.

32:04.356 --> 32:05.989
- I have no idea.

32:05.991 --> 32:07.190
- Where you going?

32:07.192 --> 32:09.026
- Some locals broke into
a supply depot.

32:09.028 --> 32:10.661
It's nothing.
- Bullshit.

32:10.663 --> 32:13.697
- All right, I'm going
to check on the kids.

32:13.699 --> 32:15.265
Harry is dead.

32:15.267 --> 32:16.533
- Who the hell's Harry?

32:16.535 --> 32:18.168
- I'll tell you on the way.
Get in.

32:24.576 --> 32:26.009
- Ewan?
- On his way.

32:26.011 --> 32:27.244
- Why would the locals
kill Harry?

32:27.246 --> 32:28.278
- He was helping Ewan.

32:28.280 --> 32:29.897
- Well, yeah,
so shoot the guy.

32:29.898 --> 32:31.515
Dump his body out in the open,
where people can see it,

32:31.517 --> 32:32.516
not out of sight.

32:32.518 --> 32:34.318
- Yeah.
- Maybe.

32:36.021 --> 32:37.654
I'm gonna go find Scott.

32:42.328 --> 32:44.661
[music playing]
- Anybody want to dance?

32:44.663 --> 32:47.130
- What?

32:47.132 --> 32:49.032
♪ ♪

32:49.034 --> 32:50.200
Brianna, come on.

32:50.202 --> 32:51.335
- You?
You want to dance?

32:51.337 --> 32:52.436
[laughs]

32:52.438 --> 32:57.074
♪ ♪

32:57.076 --> 32:59.977
- Shit.
Scott.

32:59.979 --> 33:02.446
[breathing heavily]

33:04.483 --> 33:07.284
♪ ♪

33:07.286 --> 33:08.518
- Hey, whoa!

33:08.520 --> 33:10.287
- She disappears,
and now my friend is dead,

33:10.289 --> 33:11.355
and she doesn't give a shit.

33:11.357 --> 33:12.422
How come?

33:12.424 --> 33:14.024
- Scott's dead?

33:14.026 --> 33:15.525
- My sister
is not a killer.

33:15.527 --> 33:17.461
- Everyone's a killer.

33:17.463 --> 33:22.466
♪ ♪

33:25.337 --> 33:28.438
♪ ♪

33:28.440 --> 33:30.040
- Bri!

33:30.042 --> 33:31.341
Could have done that
differently.

33:31.343 --> 33:32.609
- How much
did she have to drink?

33:32.611 --> 33:34.311
- That was her first one.

33:34.313 --> 33:35.412
[door closes]

33:35.414 --> 33:36.713
- I'm gonna kill that bitch.

33:36.715 --> 33:37.681
- Hold it.

33:37.683 --> 33:39.049
Raf!

33:39.051 --> 33:40.150
Stay here.
Watch the door.

33:40.152 --> 33:42.019
Wait for Ewan.

33:42.021 --> 33:43.587
Raf!

33:53.165 --> 33:55.465
- [laughing]

34:13.352 --> 34:15.619
- Hey.

34:21.693 --> 34:26.329
Dad?

34:26.331 --> 34:28.098
Did you come back?

34:28.100 --> 34:30.367
- What does it look like?

34:30.369 --> 34:32.536
- Wow.

34:34.440 --> 34:37.474
- All right,
it's not my damn birthday.

34:45.250 --> 34:47.551
- Hey, the kid's gone.

34:47.553 --> 34:49.653
- He wanted to remind you.

34:49.655 --> 34:51.088
- I don't understand.

34:51.090 --> 34:53.190
- Well, you had a big day.

34:53.192 --> 34:57.627
You were a blessing
to your mother and me.

34:57.629 --> 34:59.262
She says hello, by the way.

35:01.533 --> 35:04.301
- Well, tell her--
tell her I say hi back.

35:04.303 --> 35:07.471
- Towards the end,
you can see it from the moon.

35:07.473 --> 35:10.607
The only point of death
is life.

35:10.609 --> 35:12.342
- You're younger than me.

35:12.344 --> 35:15.779
- Well, I was once,
you know.

35:15.781 --> 35:17.414
- [chuckles]
I know.

35:17.416 --> 35:20.450
- So I am again.
Or I appear to be.

35:20.452 --> 35:21.818
Funny stuff, time.

35:21.820 --> 35:24.354
[laughing]

35:29.161 --> 35:30.260
- I don't understand.

35:30.262 --> 35:31.862
- No.

35:31.864 --> 35:33.697
But I bet you're going to.

35:33.699 --> 35:35.132
- What do you mean?

35:35.134 --> 35:36.833
- I think you're one of them.

35:36.835 --> 35:38.702
- One of who?

35:38.704 --> 35:40.537
- An adept.

35:40.539 --> 35:42.139
- I don't know what that is.

35:42.141 --> 35:44.341
- Me either, not completely.

35:44.343 --> 35:46.877
But it's important.

35:46.879 --> 35:49.246
- Yeah.
I mean, I can't think--

35:49.248 --> 35:50.547
- Less thinking, more feeling.

35:50.549 --> 35:52.199
That's what you need.

35:52.200 --> 35:53.850
Just let it wash over you
like a wave.

35:55.921 --> 35:58.255
- That's what Gloria said too.

35:58.257 --> 36:01.491
- You should know
that woman drinks a bit.

36:01.493 --> 36:04.628
- She had this box
of computer cards from 1970.

36:04.630 --> 36:05.829
It was just unreadable,

36:05.831 --> 36:08.265
but she knew
that the world was ending.

36:08.267 --> 36:11.434
- She knew
because she was one too.

36:11.436 --> 36:12.936
- An adept.

36:12.938 --> 36:14.571
- Be careful what you believe.

36:14.573 --> 36:16.740
Always ask yourself,
"Who thought that?"

36:16.742 --> 36:18.642
See?
- No.

36:18.644 --> 36:20.944
- You're one of them.

36:24.583 --> 36:27.884
Feel the waves, Josh.

36:27.886 --> 36:30.820
The waves are coming for you.

36:32.391 --> 36:33.657
- [exhales]

36:33.659 --> 36:35.692
-<i> It's all just math.</i>

36:35.694 --> 36:37.294
<i> It's all just vibrations.</i>

36:37.296 --> 36:39.429
<i> It's all just waves</i>
<i> of different lengths.</i>

36:39.431 --> 36:41.364
<i> And it controls your soul.</i>

36:41.366 --> 36:43.200
<i> Music, I mean,</i>

36:43.202 --> 36:44.701
<i> sound waves that play</i>
<i> your emotions</i>

36:44.703 --> 36:46.937
<i>like the bird blowing his horn.</i>

36:46.939 --> 36:49.339
- Let's just see
if Ewan is here.

36:49.341 --> 36:51.374
- Fine.
- Guys?

36:51.376 --> 36:52.576
- Hold on, bitch.
- Easy, easy.

36:52.578 --> 36:53.610
- Why'd you do it?

36:53.612 --> 36:55.212
- Matt?

36:55.214 --> 36:56.413
- You killed my friend.

36:56.415 --> 36:58.848
- Scott?
He's dead?

36:58.850 --> 37:01.851
- Stand still!
- Rafaella, put it down.

37:01.853 --> 37:02.852
Gun on the ground.

37:04.790 --> 37:06.856
You don't want to die.

37:11.563 --> 37:13.363
- You know what she did.

37:13.365 --> 37:14.931
- She didn't do anything.

37:14.933 --> 37:16.666
She wouldn't.

37:18.670 --> 37:20.003
She wouldn't ask me
to dance,

37:20.005 --> 37:22.272
and that means...

37:22.274 --> 37:23.273
shapeshifter.

37:23.275 --> 37:24.574
- Shit. Dana.

37:35.654 --> 37:37.420
- Bri, what--

37:37.422 --> 37:38.521
- What happened?

37:38.523 --> 37:39.723
- Mom, Harry and Scott
are dead.

37:39.725 --> 37:40.824
- Where's Matt?

37:40.826 --> 37:41.858
- I don't know.

37:44.529 --> 37:46.263
- Awesome place.
Where's your brother?

37:46.265 --> 37:47.530
Matt!
- Matt!

37:47.532 --> 37:48.732
We got Bri!

37:48.734 --> 37:50.467
- Ugh, this is disgusting.

37:50.469 --> 37:52.269
Matt!
- Mom, get back.

37:52.271 --> 37:54.437
Get back.
- Get away from my family!

37:54.439 --> 37:55.905
- [yells]

37:55.907 --> 37:57.974
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

37:57.976 --> 38:01.011
- Matt, put it down!

38:01.013 --> 38:03.413
- [yells]
- Oh, my God, which is which?

38:05.651 --> 38:07.717
Brianna!

38:07.719 --> 38:11.521
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

38:11.523 --> 38:13.590
- Don't shoot.
Put it down.

38:15.027 --> 38:16.926
Don't hit the wrong one.

38:23.902 --> 38:25.502
Don't.
- I got this.

38:30.475 --> 38:31.975
[gunshot]

38:31.977 --> 38:33.576
[shell casing clatters]

38:33.578 --> 38:36.012
- [panting]

38:36.014 --> 38:37.747
- [gasps]

38:39.785 --> 38:41.351
- Oh, my God, Brianna.

38:41.353 --> 38:42.085
- Bri, is that you?

38:45.023 --> 38:47.390
- Oh, my God.

38:49.361 --> 38:52.629
- You know, I've actually
had dreams where I do that.

38:54.566 --> 38:57.033
- You have not.
Take it back.

38:57.035 --> 38:58.835
- I didn't say
I was proud of it.

39:01.807 --> 39:03.740
- Honey.

39:03.742 --> 39:05.408
You're my Bri, right?

39:05.410 --> 39:07.877
Huh?
[laughs] Okay.

39:07.879 --> 39:09.879
- How did you know
which one to shoot?

39:09.881 --> 39:12.449
- She used to beat me up
all the time.

39:12.451 --> 39:14.718
She always leads with her left,
even though she's right-handed.

39:14.720 --> 39:16.386
That doesn't show up on DNA.

39:16.388 --> 39:17.520
- [chuckles]

39:17.522 --> 39:19.522
- And based on that,
you shot me.

39:19.524 --> 39:21.958
- You should be glad
you poured me all that mixer

39:21.960 --> 39:22.992
instead of the real thing.

39:22.994 --> 39:24.661
- Excuse me?
What mixer?

39:24.663 --> 39:26.429
- Forget it.
- What?

39:26.431 --> 39:28.365
- It was fake.
It was fake. It's fine.

39:28.367 --> 39:30.033
- Although I could go
for the real thing now.

39:30.035 --> 39:31.735
- I bet you could.

39:34.706 --> 39:36.673
Let's get you back.

39:51.490 --> 39:52.422
[car door opens]

39:53.492 --> 39:54.824
- Josh?

39:54.826 --> 39:56.626
Honey?

39:56.628 --> 39:59.696
You okay?
What's wrong?

39:59.698 --> 40:02.932
- They gave me peyote.

40:02.934 --> 40:06.169
It's still not clear.

40:08.540 --> 40:10.974
- Let's get you some rest,
there, son.

40:10.976 --> 40:13.710
- Honey?

40:20.619 --> 40:22.685
- Your father ordered
my death.

40:22.687 --> 40:25.989
He drugged me
and dragged me somewhere.

40:25.991 --> 40:28.024
I believe I killed
your Mr. Goat.

40:28.026 --> 40:29.559
- What is he talking about?

40:29.561 --> 40:30.727
- What the hell, Karen?

40:30.729 --> 40:32.162
The guy is high.

40:32.164 --> 40:34.497
- They cut the tetra
with something.

40:34.499 --> 40:36.599
I witnessed them murder some
people who were complaining.

40:36.601 --> 40:37.667
- That's not true.

40:37.669 --> 40:39.102
Now--now, maybe
some of it it was bad

40:39.104 --> 40:41.104
because of an accident, but--

40:41.106 --> 40:43.606
and some people died,
but I would never, ever--

40:43.608 --> 40:45.542
- You think she's gonna
believe that shit?

40:45.544 --> 40:46.943
- He's high.
He said so.

40:46.945 --> 40:49.045
He doesn't know
what he saw.

40:49.047 --> 40:51.748
You've got to believe me,
Karen.

40:51.750 --> 40:53.149
I'm your father.

40:54.453 --> 40:56.486
- Not anymore.

41:05.030 --> 41:08.198
- Matt, you're forgetting
the Harley I gave you.

41:10.469 --> 41:12.469
- No, I'm not.

41:12.471 --> 41:14.838
And you're lucky
I don't kill you myself.

41:14.840 --> 41:15.772
[slide clicks]

41:26.818 --> 41:28.785
- Karen, Karen.

41:28.787 --> 41:30.587
Take this.

41:30.589 --> 41:31.821
It's tetra.

41:31.823 --> 41:33.923
You might need it.

41:33.925 --> 41:36.926
[car door shuts,
engine turns over]

41:36.928 --> 41:38.628
-<i> You must boogie, children,</i>

41:38.630 --> 41:40.096
<i> or be ready</i>
<i> for rock without roll,</i>

41:40.098 --> 41:41.898
<i> blues without the soul.</i>

41:41.900 --> 41:43.833
<i> Just elevator music</i>
<i> as far as I can tell</i>

41:43.835 --> 41:45.702
<i> going down to hell.</i>

41:45.704 --> 41:48.037
- Jeez.
- He could lighten up.

41:48.039 --> 41:49.172
- [chuckles]

41:49.174 --> 41:51.107
[coughing]

41:53.845 --> 41:55.512
Yeah.

41:55.514 --> 41:57.714
I'm just a little run-down.

41:57.716 --> 41:59.115
We got somewhere
we got to be.

41:59.117 --> 42:00.183
- Yeah, where's that?

42:00.185 --> 42:02.018
- Wherever the Moondog is.

42:05.156 --> 42:07.123
I love you.

42:07.125 --> 42:09.692
- I love you too.

42:09.694 --> 42:11.728
- [coughing]

42:18.570 --> 42:19.903
There's blood.

42:19.905 --> 42:21.237
- Josh.

42:21.239 --> 42:24.207
<i> [tense music]</i>

42:24.209 --> 42:29.879
<i> ♪ ♪</i>
